{{!
    @template local_ai_course_assistant/privacy_notice

    Default branded privacy notice. Replaces the inline HTML echoed by
    privacy.php with a template rendered through the Output API
    (CONTRIB-10574 #78). Admins can still override the whole notice via the
    privacy_notice_override setting. Prose is the default (overridable) English.

    Context variables required for this template:
    * productfull, product, inst, today - branding / date strings
    * contactemail, privacyurl - optional contact details (sections render when set)
}}
<div class="sola-privacy-notice">

<h2>{{productfull}} Privacy Notice</h2>
<p><em>Last updated: {{today}}. Version 1.0.</em></p>

<h3>What {{product}} Is</h3>
<p>{{product}} is {{inst}}'s AI powered learning coach, built into some courses. When {{product}} is available on a course, you will see a chat widget on the course pages. You can ask {{product}} questions about the material, get practice questions, plan your study schedule, and use voice features if your course has them enabled.</p>
<p>{{product}} is not available on every course at {{inst}}. The decision to enable {{product}} on a course is made by the course developer.</p>

<h3>What Information {{product}} Collects</h3>
<p>When you use {{product}} on a course, {{inst}} records your messages, {{product}}'s responses, the course and time of each exchange, ratings and feedback you give, your study plan and reminder preferences if you create them, your chosen avatar, and a short profile summary that {{product}} generates from your conversations to personalize future sessions.</p>
<p>{{product}} also collects standard technical data needed to operate the service: your Moodle user id, IP address, browser type, and a timestamp. {{product}} does not collect your full name, email address, home address, phone number (unless you give one for reminders), payment information, or government issued identifiers.</p>

<h3>How Your Information Is Used</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Answer your questions at the moment.</li>
    <li>Personalize {{product}}'s responses to you.</li>
    <li>Improve {{product}} itself, using anonymized and aggregated data.</li>
    <li>Detect and prevent abuse.</li>
    <li>Generate analytics that help course authors improve course materials. Analytics are anonymized before they reach a human reviewer.</li>
</ol>
<p>{{inst}} does not sell your information. {{inst}} does not use your {{product}} conversations to market unrelated products to you.</p>

<h3>Who Sees Your Information</h3>
<p>To answer your questions, {{product}} works with an AI service (similar to ChatGPT or Claude) behind the scenes. Here's exactly what {{product}} shares with that service:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Your first name</li>
    <li>A summary of the course material you're studying</li>
    <li>The last 10 messages from your current {{product}} conversation</li>
    <li>Your study plan, if you've created one</li>
    <li>Your profile summary, if you've created one</li>
</ul>
<p>Here's what {{product}} never shares:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Your last name</li>
    <li>Your email address</li>
    <li>Your Moodle username or ID number</li>
    <li>Your home address</li>
    <li>Any other information that could identify you personally</li>
</ul>
<p>{{inst}} only uses AI services we have carefully reviewed and approved. Each one has a contract with {{inst}} that limits how they can use your information and forbids them from using your {{product}} conversations to train their AI.</p>

<h3>How Long {{product}} Keeps Your Information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Your current conversation is stored for the duration of your course enrollment. Only the most recent 10 turns are ever sent to the AI model.</li>
    <li>Ratings, study plans, and reminders are retained until you remove them or end your course enrollment.</li>
    <li>Anonymized analytics are retained under {{inst}}'s Records Retention Policy and cannot be linked back to you.</li>
    <li>Audit and operational logs are retained for up to 365 days.</li>
</ul>
<p>When your {{inst}} user account is deleted, all {{product}} data tied to your user id is deleted within the same operation.</p>

<h3>Your Rights</h3>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Access.</strong> View your current conversation in the widget; download a complete copy of all {{product}} data from the {{product}} user settings page.</li>
    <li><strong>Download.</strong> The user settings page offers a "Download my {{product}} data" button that produces a structured file with all your {{product}} data.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete.</strong> The same page offers course level and global delete options. Deletion is immediate.</li>
    <li><strong>Correction.</strong> {{product}} conversations are raw transcripts and are not normally amended. If a derived record looks wrong, continue using {{product}} or contact {{inst}} at the address below.</li>
    <li><strong>Object or restrict.</strong> You do not have to use {{product}}. You can remove your data at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Portability.</strong> The download is in a standard JSON format and can be imported into other systems.</li>
    <li><strong>Complaint.</strong> Contact {{inst}}. Learners in the EU, UK, Switzerland, Brazil, or Canada may also complain to their national data protection authority.</li>
</ol>

<h3>International Learners</h3>
<p>{{inst}} serves learners globally. If you are based in a region with specific data protection rules (GDPR, UK GDPR, LGPD, PIPEDA, Swiss FADP, CCPA), those rules apply to your {{product}} data. The lawful basis for processing is the performance of the education contract you have with {{inst}}, combined with {{inst}}'s legitimate interest in improving its education services.</p>

<h3>Security</h3>
<p>{{product}} lives inside {{inst}}'s Moodle platform, so you have to be logged in to use it. A few specific things we do to keep your information safe:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>In transit:</strong> When your messages travel between your device and {{product}}, they are encrypted. That means if anyone tried to intercept them, they would only see scrambled code.</li>
    <li><strong>At rest:</strong> When your information is stored, it lives in {{inst}}'s Moodle database, protected by the same security controls {{inst}} uses for the rest of your student data.</li>
    <li><strong>If something goes wrong:</strong> If we ever detect a security incident that affects your {{product}} data, {{inst}} will notify you as required by law.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Children</h3>
<p>{{product}} is available only to learners who meet the age requirements of the course they are enrolled in. {{inst}} does not knowingly collect {{product}} data from children under the age of 13.</p>

<h3>Contact</h3>
<ul>
    {{#contactemail}}
    <li>{{inst}} Contact: <a href="mailto:{{contactemail}}">{{contactemail}}</a></li>
    {{/contactemail}}
    {{#privacyurl}}
    <li>{{inst}} Privacy Page: <a href="{{privacyurl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{privacyurl}}</a></li>
    {{/privacyurl}}
    <li>Within {{product}}: open the widget, click the gear icon, open the Privacy and data section.</li>
</ul>

</div>
